---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import { Icon } from 'astro-icon/components';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="About AdBunny — AI-Optimized Banner Monetization"
  description="AdBunny builds AI-optimized banner monetization technology so publishers can turn remnant inventory into revenue with minimal engineering effort."
  keywords="AdBunny ad monetization company, AI ad tech company, banner monetization technology"
>
<section class="page-header">
  <div class="container">
    <h1>We Built AdBunny Because Remnant Inventory Deserved Better Tools</h1>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="section">
  <div class="container">
    <div class="two-col">
      <div class="col-text">
        <p>Remnant inventory monetization has historically meant static waterfalls, manual network ordering, and revenue left on the table simply because nobody had time to re-optimize the call order every week. AdBunny replaces that with an AI optimization layer that does it continuously, automatically, per impression.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="col-visual">
        <img src="/images/about-tools.png" alt="Analogy: rusty old tools replaced by a sleek modern smart tool — like AdBunny replaces static waterfalls">
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="section section-alt">
  <div class="container">
    <span class="label">Our Beliefs</span>
    <h2 class="section-title">What We Believe</h2>
    <div class="grid-3">
      <div class="card">
        <div class="card-icon"><Icon name="lucide:target" /></div>
        <h3>Integration should be simple</h3>
        <p>One JS tag should be enough — never an engineering sprint.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="card">
        <div class="card-icon"><Icon name="lucide:zap" /></div>
        <h3>Optimization should be real-time</h3>
        <p>Per impression, not on a quarterly review cycle.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="card">
        <div class="card-icon"><Icon name="lucide:handshake" /></div>
        <h3>Remnant shouldn't require trade-offs</h3>
        <p>It should just fill the gap — no choosing between your primary stack and new demand.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="section">
  <div class="container">
    <span class="label">Who We Work With</span>
    <h2 class="section-title">Who We Work With</h2>
    <p class="section-sub">Publishers and app developers monetizing remnant inventory, and ad networks, DSPs, and media buyers looking for efficient, programmatic access to that inventory.</p>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="section-cta">
  <div class="container">
    <h2>See AdBunny in Action</h2>
    <div class="hero-actions" style="justify-content:center;">
      <a href="/" class="btn btn-primary">Get Your JS Tag</a>
      <a href="/advertisers" class="btn btn-outline">Talk to Our Demand Team</a>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>
</BaseLayout>
